explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach to find the minimum window substring. It maintains a count of characters in the window and in the target string. It iterates through the string, expanding the window to the right and contracting it from the left until the window contains all characters in the target string. The minimum window is updated whenever a smaller window is found.

